1
00:00:02,875 --> 00:00:05,291
In this video, you will learn how to use

2
00:00:05,291 --> 00:00:07,750
the multi-dose Mounjaro® KwikPen®.

3
00:00:10,166 --> 00:00:14,125
It is important to properly store and handle the Mounjaro KwikPen.

4
00:00:14,125 --> 00:00:17,791
Please read the Instructions for Use that come with your KwikPen.

5
00:00:17,791 --> 00:00:21,416
Make sure to review the front and back of the Mounjaro carton

6
00:00:21,416 --> 00:00:25,916
for important information and safety instructions for this medicine.

7
00:00:25,916 --> 00:00:27,750
You should always use the medicine

8
00:00:27,750 --> 00:00:31,166
exactly as your doctor or pharmacist has told you.

9
00:00:31,166 --> 00:00:34,666
Please read the package leaflet and instructions for use

10
00:00:34,666 --> 00:00:36,916
before using the Mounjaro KwikPen

11
00:00:36,916 --> 00:00:39,416
and each time you get your refill.

12
00:00:39,416 --> 00:00:41,875
The Mounjaro KwikPen is a multi-use pen

13
00:00:41,875 --> 00:00:45,500
that contains four fixed doses of 0.6 millilitres,

14
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:47,791
one dose to be taken weekly.

15
00:00:47,791 --> 00:00:49,750
Each pen is for one patient only

16
00:00:49,750 --> 00:00:52,666
and should not be used by anyone other than you,

17
00:00:52,666 --> 00:00:54,750
even if the needle is changed.

18
00:00:54,750 --> 00:00:57,750
You may get or give others a serious infection

19
00:00:57,750 --> 00:00:59,250
if you share your pen.

20
00:00:59,250 --> 00:01:03,041
The Mounjaro KwikPen injects the medicine subcutaneously,

21
00:01:03,041 --> 00:01:05,166
or, in other words, under the skin.

22
00:01:05,166 --> 00:01:08,416
Do not transfer solution from your Mounjaro KwikPen

23
00:01:08,416 --> 00:01:09,791
into a syringe.

24
00:01:09,791 --> 00:01:12,250
Do not inject the leftover medication.

25
00:01:12,250 --> 00:01:14,916
People who are blind or have vision problems

26
00:01:14,916 --> 00:01:16,666
should not use the KwikPen

27
00:01:16,666 --> 00:01:20,000
without help from a person trained to use the KwikPen.

28
00:01:21,541 --> 00:01:24,625
Ready to learn how to use your Mounjaro KwikPen?

29
00:01:24,625 --> 00:01:27,291
Let’s begin with preparing for your injection.

30
00:01:28,541 --> 00:01:31,791
You will need these supplies for your injection:

31
00:01:31,791 --> 00:01:33,750
1 Mounjaro KwikPen

32
00:01:33,750 --> 00:01:36,041
1 KwikPen-compatible needle

33
00:01:36,041 --> 00:01:38,041
1 Alcohol swab

34
00:01:38,041 --> 00:01:39,125
Gauze

35
00:01:39,125 --> 00:01:43,666
1 Puncture-resistant container for throwing away used needles

36
00:01:45,166 --> 00:01:47,791
Remove the carton from the refrigerator.

37
00:01:49,416 --> 00:01:51,750
Remove the KwikPen from the carton.

38
00:01:52,791 --> 00:01:56,916
We will now review the steps to inject your dose of Mounjaro.

39
00:01:58,916 --> 00:02:01,291
First, get ready for your injection

40
00:02:01,291 --> 00:02:04,166
by washing your hands with soap and water.

41
00:02:06,375 --> 00:02:10,541
Pull the cap straight off and inspect the KwikPen and label.

42
00:02:10,541 --> 00:02:12,666
Check the KwikPen label to make sure

43
00:02:12,666 --> 00:02:14,875
that the medication name and dose strength

44
00:02:14,875 --> 00:02:16,291
match your prescription

45
00:02:16,291 --> 00:02:18,125
and that it has not expired.

46
00:02:18,125 --> 00:02:21,291
The medicine should be colourless to slightly yellow.

47
00:02:21,291 --> 00:02:24,250
Do not use the medicine if it has been frozen,

48
00:02:24,250 --> 00:02:27,791
is cloudy, discoloured, or has particles in it.

49
00:02:28,291 --> 00:02:32,125
Wipe the red inner seal with an alcohol swab.

50
00:02:32,166 --> 00:02:34,125
Select a new pen needle.

51
00:02:34,125 --> 00:02:37,291
Always use a new pen needle for each injection

52
00:02:37,291 --> 00:02:40,791
to help prevent infections and blocked needles.

53
00:02:40,791 --> 00:02:44,416
Pull off the paper tab from the outer needle shield.

54
00:02:44,416 --> 00:02:47,541
Push the capped pen needle straight onto the pen

55
00:02:47,541 --> 00:02:51,541
and twist the pen needle on until it is tight.

56
00:02:51,541 --> 00:02:55,166
Pull off the outer needle shield and keep it.

57
00:02:55,166 --> 00:02:57,500
This will be reused.

58
00:02:57,500 --> 00:03:00,250
Pull off the inner needle shield.

59
00:03:00,250 --> 00:03:03,375
Put it in your household trash.

60
00:03:03,375 --> 00:03:07,916
Next, slowly turn the dose knob until you hear two clicks

61
00:03:07,916 --> 00:03:11,666
and the extended line is shown in the dose window.

62
00:03:11,666 --> 00:03:14,250
This is the priming position.

63
00:03:14,250 --> 00:03:18,166
It can be corrected by turning the dose knob in either direction

64
00:03:18,166 --> 00:03:22,625
until the prime position lines up to the dose indicator.

65
00:03:22,625 --> 00:03:26,375
Then, hold your KwikPen with the needle pointing up.

66
00:03:26,375 --> 00:03:31,416
Tap the cartridge holder gently to collect air bubbles at the top.

67
00:03:31,416 --> 00:03:34,750
Next, you will need to release some medicine into the air

68
00:03:34,750 --> 00:03:37,875
by pushing the dose knob in until it stops.

69
00:03:37,875 --> 00:03:39,791
After the dose knob stops,

70
00:03:39,791 --> 00:03:43,666
begin slowly counting to 5 while holding the dose knob.

71
00:03:46,666 --> 00:03:50,375
The 0 icon must be shown in the dose window.

72
00:03:50,375 --> 00:03:52,750
Do not inject into your body.

73
00:03:52,750 --> 00:03:55,291
Priming removes air from the cartridge

74
00:03:55,291 --> 00:03:58,416
and makes sure your KwikPen is working correctly.

75
00:03:58,416 --> 00:04:02,541
You will see a drop of medicine come out
of the tip of the pen needle.

76
00:04:02,541 --> 00:04:04,125
If you do not see medicine,

77
00:04:04,125 --> 00:04:07,875
repeat this step no more than two additional times.

78
00:04:07,875 --> 00:04:10,000
If you still do not see medicine,

79
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:12,791
change the pen needle and repeat this step

80
00:04:12,791 --> 00:04:15,250
no more than one additional time.

81
00:04:15,250 --> 00:04:17,416
If you still do not see medicine,

82
00:04:17,416 --> 00:04:19,500
contact your local Lilly office

83
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:22,541
listed in the patient information leaflet.

84
00:04:24,041 --> 00:04:26,666
Now, choose your injection site.

85
00:04:26,666 --> 00:04:29,541
You or another person can inject Mounjaro

86
00:04:29,541 --> 00:04:31,541
into your thighs or stomach

87
00:04:31,541 --> 00:04:34,416
at least 5 centimetres from the belly button.

88
00:04:34,416 --> 00:04:37,291
Or you can have another person give you the injection

89
00:04:37,291 --> 00:04:39,375
in the back of your upper arm.

90
00:04:39,375 --> 00:04:42,666
Change or rotate your injection site each week.

91
00:04:42,666 --> 00:04:45,041
You may use the same area of your body,

92
00:04:45,041 --> 00:04:49,291
but be sure to choose a different injection site in that area.

93
00:04:49,291 --> 00:04:52,125
Now, turn the dose knob all the way out

94
00:04:52,125 --> 00:04:56,291
until it stops and the dose window displays the number 1.

95
00:04:56,291 --> 00:04:59,416
This position is equal to a full dose.

96
00:05:00,416 --> 00:05:03,291
Then, insert the needle into your skin.

97
00:05:03,291 --> 00:05:06,250
Inject the medicine by pushing the dose knob.

98
00:05:06,250 --> 00:05:08,875
Press the dose knob until it stops,

99
00:05:08,875 --> 00:05:12,416
and only then do you start counting slowly to 5

100
00:05:12,416 --> 00:05:14,875
while pushing down on the dose knob.

101
00:05:14,875 --> 00:05:16,791
You will know your injection is complete

102
00:05:16,791 --> 00:05:20,416
when you see the dose window display the number 0.

103
00:05:20,416 --> 00:05:22,541
Pull the needle out of your skin.

104
00:05:22,541 --> 00:05:25,541
A drop of medicine on the needle tip is normal.

105
00:05:25,541 --> 00:05:27,291
It will not affect your dose.

106
00:05:27,291 --> 00:05:30,541
Confirm the 0 icon is in the window.

107
00:05:30,541 --> 00:05:34,916
If you see the 0 icon, then you have received the full dose.

108
00:05:34,916 --> 00:05:38,166
If you do not see the 0 icon in the dose window,

109
00:05:38,166 --> 00:05:42,041
insert the needle back into your skin and finish your injection.

110
00:05:42,041 --> 00:05:44,125
Do not redial the dose.

111
00:05:45,416 --> 00:05:48,916
If you see blood after you pull the needle out of your skin,

112
00:05:48,916 --> 00:05:52,541
lightly press the injection site with gauze or a cotton ball.

113
00:05:52,541 --> 00:05:54,625
Do not rub the injection site.

114
00:05:55,500 --> 00:05:58,750
Carefully replace the outer needle shield.

115
00:05:59,791 --> 00:06:02,041
Then unscrew the capped needle.

116
00:06:02,041 --> 00:06:06,166
Do not store the pen with the needle attached to prevent leaking,

117
00:06:06,166 --> 00:06:07,625
blocking of the needle,

118
00:06:07,625 --> 00:06:09,791
or air from entering the pen.

119
00:06:11,375 --> 00:06:15,500
Throw away your used needle immediately after each injection

120
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:18,500
into your puncture-resistant container.

121
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:21,416
If you do not have a puncture-resistant container,

122
00:06:21,416 --> 00:06:23,791
you may use a household container that is:

123
00:06:23,791 --> 00:06:26,416
made of a heavy-duty plastic;

124
00:06:26,416 --> 00:06:30,041
fit with a puncture-resistant lid that can be closed tightly

125
00:06:30,041 --> 00:06:32,541
to prevent needles from coming out;

126
00:06:32,541 --> 00:06:35,041
upright and stable during use;

127
00:06:35,041 --> 00:06:36,416
leak resistant;

128
00:06:36,416 --> 00:06:39,416
and properly labelled to warn of hazardous waste

129
00:06:39,416 --> 00:06:41,041
inside the container.

130
00:06:41,041 --> 00:06:44,666
Do not recycle your used puncture-resistant container.

131
00:06:44,666 --> 00:06:46,291
Ask your healthcare provider

132
00:06:46,291 --> 00:06:49,000
or follow the community guidelines in your area

133
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,791
on how to properly dispose

134
00:06:50,791 --> 00:06:53,416
of your puncture-resistant container.

135
00:06:54,916 --> 00:06:56,500
Replace the pen cap.

136
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:59,791
Do not store the pen without the pen cap attached.

137
00:06:59,791 --> 00:07:02,666
You may store your used pen at room temperature

138
00:07:02,666 --> 00:07:06,041
up to 30°C after your injection.

139
00:07:06,041 --> 00:07:07,791
Keep away from heat.

140
00:07:08,791 --> 00:07:12,791
Throw away the pen 30 days after first use,

141
00:07:12,791 --> 00:07:15,375
even if the pen has medicine left in it.

142
00:07:15,375 --> 00:07:18,041
Your Mounjaro KwikPen should not be used

143
00:07:18,041 --> 00:07:21,166
past its 30-day in-use period.

144
00:07:21,166 --> 00:07:26,041
After 30 days, the Mounjaro KwikPen is not suitable for use.

145
00:07:26,041 --> 00:07:31,250
Throw away the used pen after receiving four weekly doses.

146
00:07:31,250 --> 00:07:33,875
There may be some medicine still left in the pen

147
00:07:33,875 --> 00:07:36,791
after the four weekly doses were administered.

148
00:07:38,916 --> 00:07:42,125
Attempting to inject any leftover medicine

149
00:07:42,125 --> 00:07:44,500
could result in an incomplete dose

150
00:07:44,500 --> 00:07:47,625
even though the pen still has medicine in it.

151
00:07:47,625 --> 00:07:51,791
Throw away the used pen in a puncture-resistant container.

152
00:07:53,916 --> 00:07:57,791
If you have any questions or concerns about administering Mounjaro,

153
00:07:57,791 --> 00:08:00,041
please contact your healthcare provider

154
00:08:00,041 --> 00:08:02,125
or Eli Lilly and Company.
